---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms of use for the independent Sample Claude Exams practice website."
>
  <section class="exam-page legal-page">
    <header class="page-intro">
      <span class="exam-page-eyebrow">Terms</span>
      <h1 class="exam-page-title">Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="section-lede">Last updated July 2, 2026.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="legal-stack">
      <section>
        <h2>Use of the site</h2>
        <p>
          Sample Claude Exams is provided for educational practice and study planning. You may use
          the public site to prepare, review concepts, and discuss readiness with a team.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>No official credential</h2>
        <p>
          The site does not issue, verify, or replace any official certification, training program,
          exam appointment, score report, badge, or partner status.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>No guarantee</h2>
        <p>
          Practice scores and explanations are provided as learning aids. They do not guarantee any
          outcome on any third-party exam, job interview, client engagement, or production project.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Responsible use</h2>
        <p>
          Do not use this site to misrepresent official affiliation, distribute unauthorized exam
          content, or imply that a practice result is an official qualification.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          The site owner may update the content, interface, question banks, and terms over time.
          Continued use after updates means you accept the updated terms.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
